      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear you, but i'm just so tired of feeling like this. honestly the doctor always just tells me \"it's fine, it's just the meds\" so i feels like i'm wasting my time. \n\nif i just drink way more water and maybe take like a double dose of magnesium to help with the shakiness, that should fix the dehydration/electrolyte thing right? it seems way more logical than waiting three days for an appointment just to be told nothing is wrong. wouldn't increasing my water intake be the most direct way to flush out any excess lithium?",
